next , let 's take a look at an interview report by this station . 
according to our understanding , under the government 's intentional manipulation , real estate prices in shanghai have become among the highest in the world . 
many government units think of all kinds of ways to forcibly tear down citizens ' residences in high - priced neighborhoods without giving reasonable compensation . 
these ordinary people who have suffered compulsory eviction , thereby losing their homes , have suddenly lost their sources of income . 
children are unable to pay tuition , and cannot attend school . 
for many years , most people who appealed to higher authorities have been sent to reform - through - labor camps for long periods of time . 
according to statistical data , shanghai is the region of china with the largest number of people appealing to higher authorities . 
han zhongming used to own a storefront , yet it was forcibly torn down . his private residence was also sold by others for profit . 
he was put under house arrest by authorities and was even detained because he appealed to higher authorities . 
having jumped from a building and slit his wrists , among other forms of protest , he was only recently released . 
chen enjuan 's storefront was also forcibly torn down by the government . 
the government hired goons to drag her family of three out of their home and used bulldozers to raze the house together with the furniture . 
she was sent to a reform - through - labor camp for nearly two years because she appealed to higher authorities . 
