helen 
mom ten years ago 
on that day ten years ago , when this teacher was taking a nap at home during noontime break , the telephone rang suddenly . 
she picked up the phone and listened , yet out came a strange rough voice : " we have caught your kid stealing a book . come here quick ! " 
coming from the other end of the line was a little girl 's crying , along with loud scolding voices of others . 
glancing over at her only daughter , who was watching tv nearby , it suddenly dawned upon her . 
obviously , a little girl must have got caught by the sales person while she was stealing a book . as she did not want to let her family know it , she must have made up a phone number at random . that was how they happened to call here . 
of course she could put down the phone and ignored the call . she could also even reprimand the other party , 
because this incident had nothing to do with her . 
however , being a teacher , she thought she might be her own student . 
the phone call gave her some rough idea that the little girl , who made the momentary slip , must be very much frightened and was facing perhaps the most horrifying situation in her life . 
hesitating for a moment , an idea suddenly occurred to her . right , just do it this way . 
so , after making sure about the bookstore 's address , she hurried there . 
just as she expected , a tearful little girl was standing in the bookstore , 
while adults nearby were yelling at her in fierce reproof . 
she rushed up to hold the poor little girl in her arms . turning around , she said to the sales person nearby : " talk to me . don 't scare the kid . " 
amid the sales person 's reluctant mutterings , she paid the fine of about a few dozen yuan before she was able to lead this little girl out of the bookstore and take a close look at that tear - smudged , terrified face . 
she laughed and took the little girl home . she gave her a good cleaning and let the girl go without asking anything . 
before she took off , she made a special effort to tell her repeatedly , if you want to read books , just come to the auntie 's place . there are many books inside . 
the little girl , who had still not yet recovered from her horror , took a close look at her and scampered away . she never reappeared . 
time went by like a rushing stream . ten years had passed in a flash before she knew it . 
having long forgotten this thing , she still lived here , leading a quiet and peaceful life . 
one day at noon , there was a series of knocks on the door . 
when she opened the door , she saw a stranger , a pretty young girl with all smiles on her face and her hands full of gifts . 
" who are you looking for ? " 
she asked doubtfully . 
in her excitement , that girl said a great deal . 
only with great efforts in following the narration of that girl , a stranger to her , did she suddenly realize that she was that little girl of that year . she had graduated smoothly from college after ten years and now took this trip purposely to visit her . 
with her eyes glistening with tears , the young girl said softly : " though i have never understood even today why you were willing to pretend to be my mom to help me out , i have always felt all these ten years that i want to call you mom . " 
the teacher 's eyes also grew blurry . 
she asked curiously : " if i had not helped you , what would have happened ? " 
the girl 's face immediately darkened . she gently shook her head and said : " i am not sure . i could have done something foolish and might have even committed suicide . " 
the teacher 's heart trembled , and she started to feel rejoiced secretly . 
the decision she made on the spur of the moment that year turned out to have had such an impact on one person 's life . 
looking at the happy smile on the girl 's face , she also smiled . 
zhang xiwen 
when this world is filled with lies and fraud like junk text messages everywhere , buddha said , if i don 't go to hell , who else goes to hell . 
if anyone has done this , then congratulations , because he could become buddha earlier . 
human beings at their birth are naturally good . 
compassion lies in the heart of every human being . 
the moral degeneration of the world is getting worse day by day . people are not what they were in times past . 
perhaps only self - sacrificing buddha can do some good deeds . 
observation on military situation : how long would iran be able to hold on against us military air strikes ? 
yun feiquan 
if we liken a traditional war of attrition to making the enemy bleed to death , then modern warfare is firing a bullet right into the enemy 's head at the outset , turning it into a " vegetable " with no time to bleed . 
the difference between iran and the us in military power is not in the numbers but in their understanding of modern warfare . 
iran , which fought an eight - year war with iraq without any distinguishable winner , does not seem to understand the real significance of modern high - tech warfare . 
the british international intelligence review recently mentioned , after analyzing us military deployments , that us troops are preparing to launch a large - scale air strike on iran ... 
the current status of the iranian air force is rather worrisome . 
the current status of the iranian air force is very similar to the pre - war iraqi air force $date . 
the home country does not have the ability to develop modern weapons independently and is also under the arms embargo imposed by the west . 
upon the breakout of war , it is quite uncertain whether the old and outdated planes of the iranian air force could take off and fight the us military . 
currently , iran 's air defense system is chiefly composed of the air force and land - based air defense force of iran 's regular military as well as the air defense force of the revolutionary guard corps . 
among these , the iranian air force is currently $number strong and has $number fighter planes of various models . 
the main plane models are us - made f-4 phantoms , f-5 tigers , and f-14 tomcats , and russian - made mig-29s , among others . 
the land - based air defense forces are mainly equipped with us - made hawk , british - made arrow , and some russian - made sam series surface - to - air missiles . 
analyzing the current status of the iranian air defense forces , harold hutchinson , a us military expert , khramchikhin , a military expert at russia 's institute of political and military analysis , and others think that looking at the current situation , there are still some holes in iran 's air defense capabilities and its air defense system construction . 
hutchinson thinks that in terms of overall real power , the iranian air force is absolutely not at the same level as the us military . 
the large number of us - made fighter planes iran has are inoperable due to lack of spare parts , upgrades , and maintenance . 
of the f-14 fighters , once considered the trump of the iranian air force , currently only $number - plus can take off . 
it is also questionable whether the aim-54 phoenix missiles that they carry , which are said to have over - the - horizon attack capability , are reliable in actual battle . 
khramchikhin mentioned that the air defense missile systems that the us provided to iran $date and $date have lost combat power due to lack of spare parts . 
some other non - system air defense weapons acquired from russia and other countries are no match for the us military , which is capable of electromagnetic countermeasures . 
scraping it together has an effect on combat power . 
the iranian government obviously also realizes that its fate in war depends on its ability to defend the home skies . in a last - minute effort to update its weaponry , it scraped together all it could get to reinforce its air defense system . 
from what can be seen at present , its methods can be summarized into two . 
$number , work hard to conceal key nuclear facilities to enhance its capability to defend against attacks . 
according to a report by the british newspaper the times , iran has concealed the core parts of nuclear facilities such as the natanz nuclear plant and isfahan uranium enrichment center as deep as $number meters underground and encased them with $number - meter thick cement protection . 
however , the us military is a step ahead , having seen the effects of underground bunkers during the $number gulf war in defending against air strikes , it rushed development of various kinds of ground penetrating bombs . 
after more than ten years of targeted research , the us military now has a complete package of combat methodology and weapons to deal with reinforced underground bunkers . 
iran has recently also bought large quantities of air defense weaponry from russia . 
since the end of last year , the iranian government has made successive agreements with russia to purchase the pechora-2a air defense missile system , along with $number sets of the tor - m1 air defense missile system worth $number us dollars . 
however , modern warfare is a competition between systems . 
the various air strike weapons of the us military were all developed independently by their own country . furthermore , after years of real war experience , they have been adapted into a set of impressive and effective war machines . 
in contrast , whether the " new weapons " iran gathered from other countries and put together can become a combat force within such short period of time is still an issue . 
iran is not lagging behind in weapons only . 
the army field manual published by the us military $date proposed for $number time the doctrine of " air land battle , " which emphasizes attacking the enemy 's deeply strategic and high - value targets using air superiority to paralyze the enemy 's command system at the start of the war so that the enemy can become nothing more than " meat on the chopping board " no matter how powerful its regular military strength . 
in the $number gulf war , the $number kosovo war , and the $number iraq war , the us military cared not about how many planes the enemy had but the range of its own tomahawk cruise missiles . 
although the iranian government has been preparing for possible air strikes and has started taking measures to enhance its air defense capabilities , iran , which fought an eight - year war with iraq without any distinguishable winner , does not seem to understand the real significance of modern high - tech warfare . 
along with the us military 's progress in recent years in military transformation work , the us military 's air strike operations already completely differ from vietnam war era carpet bombing , depending instead on various kinds of high - tech weapons and on modern information technology - based high precision and full depth air attacks . 
confronted with such air strikes , it is still unknown how long iran 's land - based air defense system would be able to hold on . 
source : cri online - " world news journal " 
