reporter 's note : google shaking microsoft 's throne ? 
huizhengyi 
computers have doubtlessly become a necessity for modern people in their life and work . 
however , while everybody uses a computer skillfully , only a handful of people actually know the operating principle of a computer . 
just as using a " foolproof " camera , as long as the interface is friendly and software is easy to use , most beginners can equally feel comfortable operating such a black box as a computer . 
therefore , pc 's manufacturer - installed original software will often determine the usage habits of most consumers . 
it is exactly through this measure that microsoft commands a solid control of the pc operating system market . 
now , google , microsoft 's new rival , also intends to have its finger in the pie through this means . 
a well - known economics media outfit recently used a very interesting metaphor for this . 
" dell , hewlett packard , and other computer manufacturers started to treat their computer products as supermarket shelves and charge software companies " shelving fees . " 
winning bidders can have their software appear in the 'critical ten minutes ' when users start their new computers so as to guide consumers to use their products . 
this mode of charging fees resembles the way supermarkets charge food suppliers shelving fees . " 
doubtlessly , this phenomenon indicates microsoft 's control is being loosened . 
microsoft 's managers warned bill gates that if google began to pay pc manufacturers to have their computers installed with google software when they are shipped out , then microsoft 's hegemony will eventually be threatened . 
no matter what will be the outcome of the situation , microsoft 's stable and easy days as number one may become history . 
after all , it is easier to win the throne than to keep the throne . 
