the two belligerent parties in sri lanka agreed to hold negotiations in geneva late this month 
afp , colombo , $number . 
norway , as a mediator for the peace process , said that belligerent groups in sri lanka agreed to hold negotiations in geneva , switzerland , on the $number of this month , finally breaking the stalemate on negotiations - which has stagnated for three years - to end the several dozen years of bloody ethnic conflicts pursued by the parties . 
this breakthrough was achieved after solheim , a norwegian envoy for peace , met with balasingham , a negotiation representative for the liberation tigers of tamil eelam , in london . 
the norwegian embassy here said in a statement that " the belligerent parties in sri lanka , that is the government of sri lanka and the liberation tigers of tamil eelam , have requested the norwegian government to assist in holding two - day negotiations from $date to $number in geneva . " 
the two - day negotiations will focus on how to strengthen the cease - fire agreement effected on $date ; this agreement has not been fully complied with by both sides . 
the norwegian embassy pointed out that , " both sides will discuss how to improve the implementation of the cease - fire agreement , which is $number time for both sides to have face - to - face negotiations at such a high level . " 
solheim said that he will lead a norwegian delegation participating in the negotiations ; balasingham will lead the four delegates of the liberation tigers of tamil eelam , and the health minister will be the head of the government ( delegation ) of sri lanka . 
he said , " this is a small step but an important one on the road of peace , and it is expected to be difficult for the negotiation process . " 
the previous face - to - face negotiations for resolving the ethnic conflicts in sri lanka were held in $date , in japan , but the liberation tigers of tamil eelam cancelled $number round of negotiations originally scheduled for thailand in $date . 
