signs of bird flu emerge everywhere in europe , and people are in a panic in nigeria 
afp , brussels , $number . 
signs of bird flu virus continue to emerge in europe and send people into panic . 
the executive committee of the european union has passed a resolution for the establishment of additional " buffer area " controls , including all areas of countries where the virus has been discovered for control , and forbidding all trade and transportation of poultries and bird species . 
the bird flu breakouts continue to spread to more chicken farms following $number day since the deadly h5n1 virus was discovered in nigeria , africa , and tracks demonstrate that it has crossed the northern border of nigeria and entered into niger . 
egyptian officials are investigating the sudden mass death of chickens on a chicken farm in the south , and there is concern that the virus might continue to spread . 
chicken meat markets in europe are falling to a great extent because of the impact of the virus event . the executive committee of the european union stressed that there is no reason to panic . 
jipu ruinuo , an executive member of the committee responsible for sanitation and food safety , said that it is understandable for people to be concerned about the event but there is no need for overreaction . 
the executive committee of the european union has issued a new regulation and listed all of the european areas where the virus has been discovered as " buffer areas " after passing a previous resolution about the establishment of a three - kilometer protection area and ten - kilometer warning area around every virus discovery spot . 
an official for the european union , who preferred to remain anonymous , pointed out that everyone is very nervous , and processing news from everywhere in europe about suspicions of breakouts of the epidemic . 
until now , the h5n1 virus has been discovered in european regions including austria , bulgaria , croatia , germany , greece , italy , romania , slovenia , ukraine , and russia , and has been discovered almost exclusively in groups of wild swans . 
on the $number , romania discovered its $number epidemic case , and slovenia , austria , greece , and ruegen island in germany have also discovered new epidemic cases . 
the bird flu virus was discovered in the bodies of two ducks in southern italy , which are $number poultry infected with the h5n1 virus in the european region , aside from wild swans . 
the greatest concern that european union officials have is those migrant birds that will be flying back from africa . 
the nigerian government is strengthening its work to prevent the human infection of the virus on the african continent . 
the nigerian government announced that all poultries and bird species must be destroyed within a five - kilometer area of where an infected farm is discovered , regardless of whether they are threatened by the virus or not . 
the government of niger , its neighbor country , has announced a national warning state , and made an emergency plan by providing $number usd to monitor the border areas with nigeria . 
the newly established national emergency committee stated that they have received a report that nearly $number poultries and bird species are dead in magaria , a loosely guarded area between the two countries . 
