now , let us watch the coverage by our station . 
according to information , real estate prices in shanghai have become one of the world 's highest under the government 's speculation . 
many government agencies try every means to forcibly demolish the houses and resettle residents in high - priced areas , but fail to provide them with reasonable compensation . 
these people who lost their homes due to mandatory demolition and resettlement suddenly lost their income source . 
they cannot afford their children 's tuition fees , so they are afraid to go to school . 
throughout the years , the majority of the people have earned themselves reform through education time by appealing for intervention from higher authorities . 
according to statistics , shanghai is the area in china that has the highest number of people who appeal for intervention from higher authorities . 
han zhongming originally owned a store , but it was torn down by force ; even his private residence was resold at a profit . 
he was under house arrest and was even detained by the authorities for appealing for help from higher authorities . 
he protested by committing suicide by jumping off a building and cutting his wrist . he was only released recently . 
chen enjuan 's store was also forcibly torn down by the government . 
the government hired gangsters to drag the three people in her household outside , and then used a forklift to destroy her house , together with the furniture . 
she had been reeducated through labor for nearly two years for appealing to higher authorities for help . 
when talking about her support for the hunger strike , chen enjuan said that besides protesting against the gang - like behavior of the government , 
attorney gao has given us much legal assistance and helped us selflessly . 
our civil rights protest is to demand democracy , because we are also concerned about our next generation . 
the generation before us has already suffered dearly . we need to fight for our next generation , so that they will not be persecuted . thus , we need to participate in the civil rights protest and cannot give up . 
