china to implement protection regulation on dissemination rights for information networks 
xinhua news agency , beijing , $date ( reporters : zhou wei and li fei ) . many networks and websites currently rely on republishing a lot of news and reports from newspapers and magazines to increase their click rates , but many of them are neither authorized , nor pay related fees . to cope with this , director of the copyright department of the state copyright bureau wang ziqiang said in a press conference , held by the news office of the state council on the $number , that the state cou 
wang ziqiang said that according to existing laws and regulations , regarding those works published in newspapers , as long as their authors did not state that " they cannot be used , " newspapers can use those works without their authors ' permission , but at the same time should pay them , and the state copyright bureau has made the payment standard specifically for newspaper reprint practices according to the law . 
however , according to regulations in existing laws , newspapers have the right to such legal permissions , but the internet currently does not have rights for such legal permissions . 
according to related interpretations made by the people 's supreme court , the legal permission for newspaper reprints is applied to the internet , i.e. to any small or short articles published in newspapers or on the internet , whose authors did not state that " they cannot be used , " the internet can use them without permission , but at the same time needs to pay their authors . 
but because the legal interpretation does not determine the payment standard , the internet has not made payments when it used those works in practice . 
" regarding whether the internet use of published small or short works applies to the legal permission , it still needs to be determined according to the laws . " 
wang ziqiang said : " whether it will be included in a category of law depends on the confirmation of the implementation of the protection regulation on dissemination rights for information networks this year . " 
