mom of ten years ago 
helen li 
read this article , and wanted to share it with people . 
this is not an impulsion , but warmness and kindness staying in my heart for a long time . 
i ask myself if it were me , what i would do . 
the answer is very clear . i would hang up the phone , " you dialed a wrong number . " 
this year i have been thinking about what really counts for helping people . 
i have given up tentative conduct , such as donations of cash or items . 
some friend said a couple of days ago that he has no time to take care of himself , not mention to help people , even though his desire for providing help is bigger than his ability . 
wish you a happy day : ) 
helen 
mom of ten years ago 
it was one day ten years ago when this teacher was taking a nap by using the rest time at noon . suddenly , the phone rang . 
she picked up the phone , and heard a strange and rude voice : " your child stole a book , and we caught her . come and hurry up ! " 
the crying noise of a little girl and denouncing voices from others came out of the handset . 
she understood the thing immediately when she turned her head and looked at her only daughter , who was watching tv . 
there must be a little girl who was caught by the saleswoman for stealing a book . she does not want her family members to know this , so she made up a phone number , and a phone call happens to come here . 
she could of course hang up the phone and give no response , and even scold the other side . 
because this thing has nothing to do with her . 
but she herself is a teacher ; maybe that girl is one of her pupils . 
she could probably imagine through the phone that that little girl , who made a wrong decision at that moment , must be very panicked , and may be facing the most terrible situation of her life . 
after she hesitated for a moment , she suddenly had an idea in her mind . yes , i will do it this way . 
then , she asked for the detailed address of the bookstore , and hurried there . 
as she expected , a little girl with tear stains all over her face was standing in the bookstore . 
and those adults standing around were scolding her ferociously in loud voices . 
she rushed to the poor little girl and held her in her arms , and turned her head to the sales clerks around , and said : " talk to me if you have something to say . do not terrify the child . " 
she took the little girl with her and walked out of the bookstore after she paid out several dozen yuan as a fine , while the sales clerks were whispering reluctantly . then , she could clearly see the face messed with tears and panic . 
she smiled , and brought the little girl home . she cleaned her up thoroughly and let her go without asking anything . 
she especially urged her before she left , " if you want to read books , you could come here , auntie 's home has a lot of books . " 
the little girl , who was still in a panic , gazed at her deeply before running away , and never showed up again . 
time passes as quickly as running water , and a period of ten years has passed in a flash without notice . 
she had forgotten the thing a long time ago , and still lives there with a calm and serene life . 
one afternoon , knocking noises came from outside the door . 
a young and strange girl with a pretty face appeared when she opened the door . she had a big smile on her face and was holding a big pile of gifts in her hands . 
" who are you looking for ? " 
she asked with doubt . 
the girl was moved and talked with a lot of words . 
it was not easy for her to find out from the strange girl 's talking that she was the little girl of that year . ten years after , she had graduated from a university without any difficulties , and now she had made a special trip to see her . 
the young girl said with a soft voice and tears in her eyes : " although i still don 't understand why you were willing to pretend to be my mom and save me , during these $number years , i have always felt that i want to call you mom . " 
the teacher 's eyes also started to become blurred . 
" if i did not help you that day , what was going to happen to you ? " she asked with curiosity . 
the face of the girl suddenly became gloomy . she shook her head slightly and said , " i cannot explain it clearly , i might have done a stupid thing or even killed myself . " 
the teacher felt a sudden jump in her heart , and began to rejoice in her mind . 
the decision she made at that moment in that year could even impact a person in her life . 
looking at the happy smile on the face of that girl , she also smiled with her . 
zhang xiwen 
the world is filled with lies and frauds in trash short - text messages flying everywhere . buddha said , " if i do not enter hell , who would enter hell , " 
anyone who does this , then , congratulate him , he can become a buddha sooner . 
any human being has a kind personality when he starts his life . 
everyone has a sympathetic heart . 
now social ethics is going down day by day , and human hearts are not what they were in those old days . 
maybe only selfless buddha can do something good . 
military situation observation : how long can iran hold up under air attacks by us armed forces ? 
yun feiquan 
if traditional warfare of attrition is described as letting an opponent bleed to death , then modern warfare is shooting at the head of an opponent $number and making him a " human vegetable " before he bleeds . 
the gap between the military capabilities of iran and the united states is not their quantities , but understanding of modern warfare . 
iran , which came to a draw with iraq in an eight - year war , does not seem to understand the real meaning of modern high - tech warfare . 
the british international intelligence comments pointed out a few days ago , after it analyzed the state of us armed forces movements , that the us armed forces are preparing to launch large - scale air attacks on iran ... 
the current status of the iranian air force is worrisome . 
the present status of the iranian air forces is quite similar with that of the iraqi air force before the iraq war $date . 
iran itself does not have the capacity to independently develop modern weapons , and is embargoed from importing weapons from the west . 
once a war breaks out , it is really a question of whether those old and obsolete aircrafts of the iranian air force could take off to confront the us armed forces . 
currently , the iranian air defense system is mainly composed of the air force and ground air defense troops of the iranian regular armed forces , and the air - defense forces of the revolutionary guard corps . 
among them , the iranian air forces have around $number troops , and $number various types of combat aircrafts . 
their primary aircraft models include the f-4 " phantom , " f-5 " tiger , " and f-14 " tomcat " made by the us and the mig-29 made by russia , etc. 
the ground air defense troops are mainly equipped with surface to air missiles , including the us " hawk , " british " javelin " and some of the russian " sam " series of missiles . 
harold hutchinson , a us military expert , and helamuchisin , a military expert from russia 's politics and military analysis institute , analyzed the current status of the iranian air defense forces , and think that the iranian air defense capacities and air defense system and construction still have some loopholes in the current status . 
hutchinson thinks that the iranian air forces are not at all at the same level with the us armed forces from the perspective of whole actual strength . 
a lot of the iranian combat aircrafts made by the us cannot be used because of lack of parts , upgrades , and maintenance . 
the f-14 fighter planes previously regarded as the elite ones in the iranian air force only have about ten capable of taking off from the ground . 
the combat reliability of aim $number " phoenix " missiles , claimed to be capable of over - the - horizon attacks , is also doubtful . 
helamuchisin pointed out that those iranian air defense missile systems provided by the us $date of the last century have lost their combat powers because of lack of spare parts . 
and other air defense weapons that do not form any systems , such as weapons obtained from russia and other countries , have no capabilities at all to cope with the us armed forces , which have powerful electromagnetic combat capabilities . 
scrappy weapons affect combat power 
apparently , the iranian government realizes that its fate in a war depends on whether it is capable of defending the sky over its head , and is starting to prepare only at the last moment , scrape weapons together , and strengthen its air defense system . 
its methods can be summed up as the two strategies from the current state : 
$number one is to conceal important nuclear facilities as much as possible and strengthen their anti - strike capabilities . 
according to a report from the british newspaper times , iran has hidden core parts of its nuclear facilities $number meters under ground and added a protection shell of $number - meter - thick cement , including the nuclear plant in natanz and the uranium enrichment center in isfahan . 
but the us armed forces have taken a strategy in advance . they saw the effects of underground bunkers in anti - air attack combat as early as during the gulf war $date , and have rushed developing various ground - penetrating bombs . 
through $number years ' studies on targets , the us armed forces have had a whole set of combat methods and weapons coping with underground consolidated bunkers . 
iran has also purchased a lot of advanced air defense weapons from russia in recent years . 
since the end of last year , the iranian government has reached agreements with russia , one after another , for the purchase of the pechora-2a air defense missile system and $number sets of " dower " air defense missile systems , worth $number us dollars . 
however , a modern war is a rivalry between systems . 
various us armed forces air - attack weapons are developed by the us itself , and they have been sharpened and become a set of war machines with outstanding effects after years of tests in actual warfare . 
and those " new weapons " scraped together by iran from other countries are still a question of whether they can form combat power in a short time . 
weapons are not iran 's only gap . 
combat outlines , published by the us armed forces $date , $number came up with the idea of " integrated air - ground warfare , " and stressed the use of air supremacy to strike high - value targets in an enemy 's strategic depth area , paralyzing the enemy 's command system at the beginning of a war , and making him as " meat on the cutting board " even though he has very powerful conventional forces . 
in the gulf war $date , kosovo war $date , and the iraq war $date , what the us armed forces paid attention to was not how many aircrafts the opponents had , but the firing range of their own " tomahawk " cruise missile . 
although the iranian government has prepared for possible air attacks and started to take measures to strengthen air defense capabilities , iran , which came to a draw with iraq in an eight - year war , does not seem to understand the real meaning of modern high - tech warfare . 
with the development of us armed forces military transition work in recent years , the air - attack activities of the us armed forces are totally different from the carpet bombing method in the vietnam war era , and rely on various new high - tech weapons and high - precision and whole - depth air strikes that are based on modern information technology . 
how long the iranian ground air defense system can sustain itself in this kind of air strikes is still an unknown element . 
source : international online - world news journal 
