rivaling microsoft by uniting with google ; is dell collecting a " stocking fee ? " 
yun feiquan 
dell inc . ( us ; dell ) and google confirmed on tuesday that dell is testing personal computers loaded with google 's software packages . 
this move might pose a serious threat to the dominant status of microsoft corp. , msft , in the pc software market . 
jess blackburn , the news spokesman for dell corporation , said that the corporation is assessing google 's software . 
after the software is installed , pc users can use the software to search not only on the internet , but also for information stored on their pcs . 
blackburn confirmed that the software the corporation is testing includes the dell homepage supported by google , google 's desktop search system and google 's toolbar . 
google 's news spokesman , jon murchinson , also confirmed at the same time that his company is testing a batch of software , developed by google , with dell . 
as the wall street journal previously reported , google - the it new baron - is negotiating with dell and hewlett - packard co . , and is trying to persuade these computer manufacturing giants to install google 's software for their computers . 
according to an internal source cited by the wall street journal , to achieve the goal , google might pay $number dollars to dell in the coming three years . 
however , neither company has disclosed related details . 
and also , the hewlett - packard side has refused to make a comment on it . 
the microsoft corporation news spokesman , neil charney , refused to make a comment on the news mentioned above . 
microsoft is currently planning to promote its next - generation search tool for the windows operating system and strengthen development of its online business . 
on the day the news was released , google 's stock price fell another $number , dropping to $number dollars . 
the microsoft 's stock price fell $number , and closed at $number dollars on that day . 
some analysts pointed out that google is anxious to seek another direction of expansion in addition to network searches , and that its integration with dell and other pc giants might prompt google to threaten microsoft 's core business . 
matt rosoff , an analyst on microsoft 's direction at a market investigation and research company , said that microsoft is absolutely concerned and worried that google is eager to expand its new income sources . 
but some analysts do not think so . 
charles di bona , an analyst at market analysis company sanford c. bernstein , pointed out that it is too early for google to shake microsoft 's dominant status . 
reporter 's journal : google shakes microsoft 's domination ? 
hui zhengyi 
there is no doubt that computers have become necessities in the life and work of modern people . 
however , there is only a minority of people who understand the working rationale of computers , when everyone can skillfully operate them . 
like they use " dummy " cameras , most " newbies " can play the black boxes well as long as those boxes have friendly interfaces , and convenient and simple software . 
thus , original software installed on a pc manufacturer 's products can usually determine most consumers ' using habits . 
it is through this measure that microsoft has tightly controlled the pc operating system market . 
right now , google , a new rival of microsoft , tends to share part of the market through the same measure . 
a well - known economics medium in taiwan recently made a very interesting metaphor . 
" computer manufacturers including dell and hewlett - packard are starting to use computers like shelves in a supermarket and are collecting the " stocking fee " from software companies . 
a successful bidder can make its own software show up in the 'critical ten minutes ' when users turn on their new computers , and guide consumers to use its products . 
this kind of fee collection mode is like how a supermarket collects stocking fees from food manufacturers . 
this phenomenon demonstrates that microsoft 's control power is beginning to loosen without a doubt . 
managers at microsoft have warned bill gates that the microsoft 's hegemonic status will eventually be threatened if google starts to pay pc manufacturers for installation of google 's software on their computer products . 
no matter what the outcome is , the number one status that microsoft has been enjoying in those comfortable days may become history . 
after all , it is easy to become dominant , but it is difficult to maintain a dominant status . 
