hasan al - bushra , advisor to the who eastern mediterranean region , said that at present dead birds infected with the h5n1 bird flu virus have been discovered in cairo and giza in central egypt and three areas in minya in the country 's south . the responsible departments of the egyptian government have begun to slaughter domestic fowl that could be infected with bird flu . 
