& lt ; headline & gt ; a mother ten years in the past 
& lt ; poster & gt ; helen li 
i saw this article and decided to share it with you ; 
this is not a momentary impulse , but rather a warm kindheartedness that has long existed in the heart . 
i asked myself what i would do if it were me . 
the answer is very clear . i would way , " you have the wrong number " and hang up the telephone . 
i 've been thinking all this year about how one can actually help someone . 
i have already given up on actions such as donating money or goods . 
a couple days ago a friend said , " i already have no spare time to take care of myself . as for helping people , the heart is there by the means are not . " 
have a nice day : ) 
helen 
a mother ten years in the past 
it was a day ten years ago . the teacher was using the lunch break to nap at home , when suddenly the telephone rang . 
she answered and heard an unfamiliar rough voice from the receiver : " your child stole a book and we caught her . come over right away ! " 
the crying of a little girl could also be heard though the receiver , as well as the sound of somebody nearby scolding her . 
she turned her head to look at her only daughter watching the television and then immediately understood what was happening . 
clearly , a little girl had been caught by a store clerk stealing a book and did not want her family to find out , so she dialed a number at random and happened to call there . 
of course , she could hang up and forget about it , or even reprimand the party on the other line , 
because this affair had absolutely nothing to do with her . 
but she was a teacher , and it could be that it was one of her students . 
through the telephone , she could roughly imagine that the little girl who had made a mistake on the spur of the moment was surely terrified , since she was facing what could be life 's most frightening circumstance . 
after hesitating a moment , a thought suddenly came to her mind . yes , she would do it . 
thereupon , after asking the bookstore 's address , she rushed over there . 
just as she had anticipated , standing in the bookstore was a little girl with a face full of tears . 
the adults beside her were ferociously and loudly scolding her . 
she instantly rushed forward and gathered the pitiful little girl into her arms , then turned toward the nearby store clerk and said : " whatever you have to say you can say to me . you shouldn 't frighten children . " 
during the muttering of the somewhat unwilling store clerk , she paid the fine of less than $number yuan and then , with the little girl in hand , walked out of the store where she could see clearly the face overwhelmed by panic and tears . 
she smiled and returned home with the little girl where she tidied her up without asking anything , then let the little girl leave , 
as the little girl was about to go , she also made a point of urging , " if you want to read a book , then come here to auntie 's house . there are lots of books here . ' 
the still badly shaken little girl looked are her deeply for a moment , then dashed off , after which she never came back . 
time rushed by like running water . imperceptibly , ten years went by in a flash . 
she had forgotten the incident , still living there as before , she led a calm and peaceful life . 
one afternoon , there was a knocking on the outside door . 
opening the door to her apartment , she saw a pretty young woman she did not know . the girl was smiling broadly and in her hands she held a stack of presents . 
" who are you looking for ? " 
she asked with uncertainty . 
the young girl excitedly gave a long explanation . 
to her surprise , from the unfamiliar young lady 's story she suddenly realized that the young woman was actually the little girl from that year . ten years later , she had graduated from university without difficulty and had now come especially to call on her . 
the young woman 's eyes glistened with tears as she said in a gentle voice : " although i still don 't understand even today why you were willing to pass yourself off as my mother and come to my rescue , but for the last ten years i had a constant feeling that i wanted to cry out ' mother ' to you . " 
the teacher 's eyes started to cloud over as well . 
somewhat curious , she asked : " if i hadn 't helped you that day , what would have been the result ? " 
the young woman 's face instantly darkened and she lightly shook her head , saying : " i 'm not sure . maybe i would have gone on doing stupid things , or i might even have died . " 
a violent shiver went through the teacher 's heart , then she rejoiced to herself . 
the impetuous decision that she had made back then had unexpectedly had such an influence on a person 's entire life . 
looking at the happy smile on the young woman 's face , she also began to smile . 
& lt ; poster & gt ; zhang xiwen 
while the world is full of lies and cheating that fill the air like junk messages , buddha says , " who would enter hell but i would enter it ... " 
whoever is willing to do that , i congratulate him . he will achieve buddhahood sooner . 
human nature is good at the outset . 
everybody has a compassionate heart . 
the world is going to the dogs and people 's hearts have changed . 
perhaps only by abandoning one 's own buddha can one do a little good . 
& lt ; headline & gt ; military observation : how long can iran hold out under us air attacks ? 
& lt ; poster & gt ; yun feiquan 
if we describe conventional war of attrition as causing the opponent to bleed to death , then from the outset modern warfare consists of shooting a gun toward the opponent 's head in order to render him a " vegetable " even before there is time to bleed . 
the disparity between the military capabilities of iran and the us is not one of quantity , but rather in the understanding of modern war . 
iran , which fought a victorless eight - year war with iraq , seems not yet to have understood the true significance of modern hi - tech warfare . 
following an analysis of us military deployments , britain 's " international intelligence - - commentary " recently said that the us military is carrying out preparations to launch a large scale air assault on iran ...... 
the current status of iran 's air force is cause for concern . 
the present situation of iran 's air force is quite similar to that of iraq 's air force prior to the $number war . 
the country does not possess the capacity to research and develop modern weapons on its own and is also under an arms embargo imposed by the west . 
once war breaks out , it is uncertain whether the antiquated planes in iran 's air force will be able to take to the air to engage us forces . 
at present , iran 's air - defense system consists primarily of an air force belonging to iran 's regular forces , the land - based air - defense force and the air - defense capacity of the revolutionary guard . 
of these , iran 's air force presently has a manpower of $number and $number aircraft of various models . 
the most important aircraft models include us - manufactured f-4 phantoms , f5 tigers , f-14 tomcats and russian - manufactured mig-29s . 
the land - based air - defense force is primarily equipped with surface - to - air missiles of the us - manufactured hawk series and the british rapier series , as well as a portion belong to the russian - manufactured sam series . 
with regards to the current status of iran 's air - defense strength , analysis by individuals such as the us military expert harold hutchison and military expert [ hela muqixin ] of the [ russian political and military research institute ] indicates that , viewed from the present situation , there are still holes in iran 's air - defense capabilities and air - defense system . 
hutchison says that with respect to overall capabilities , iran 's air force simply is not on the same level as the us air force . 
a large number of the us - manufactured jetfighters that iran is equipped with cannot be used because of a lack of spare parts and upgrading . 
the f-14 fighter was once the trump card of iran 's air force , but today there are only ten or so that are able to fly . 
the dependability in actual combat of the aim-54 phoenix missiles they carry , known for their ultra - long distance attack capabilities , is also doubtful . 
[ hela muqixin ] points out however that the air - defense missile systems provided to iran by the us $date and $date have lost their warfare capabilities because of a lack of spare parts . 
in addition , the other non - systematic air - defense weapons obtained from russia and other countries are simply incapable of countering us forces possessing powerful electromagnetic countermeasure capabilities . 
scraping together a military affects battle capability 
clearly , iran 's government is also aware that its fate in a conflict depends upon whether it can defend the sky above and it has been carrying out $number - hour preparations by scraping together whatever it can find in order to build up its air - defense system . 
at present , its methods can be summarized into two devices : 
$number is an all - out effort to conceal key nuclear facilities and beef up their defense capabilities . 
according to a report in the british newspaper the times , iran has hidden the natanz nuclear facility , the isfahan uranium enrichment center and other core components of their nuclear facilities eighteen meters underground and added a two - meter thick concrete protection shell . 
but the us military is one step ahead . as early as the $number persian gulf war , it saw the effectiveness of underground bunkers in anti - aircraft defense and rushed to develop various types of earth - penetrating bombs . 
after ten years of focused research , the us military has a full complement of strategies and weapons to counter reinforced underground bunkers . 
iran has recently also bought a large amount of advanced air - defense weapons from russia . 
since the end of last year , iran 's government has reached a series of agreements with russia to purchase pechora-2a air defense missile systems as well as $number tor - m1 air - defense missile systems valued at us $ 7 0 0 m . 
however , modern warfare is a contest of system against system . 
the various air - attack weapons of the us military have all been developed by the country itself for its own benefit and , through many years of perfectioning in actual combat , they have been molded into an impressive war machine . 
on the other hand , iran 's " up - to - date weapons " have been scraped together from other countries . whether or not they can be made combat effective in such a short time is still in question . 
iran 's lags behind not only in weapons 
the concept of " air - land battle " was $number raised in " operations " , published by the us military $date . it stresses reliance on strength in the air to carry out attacks against the enemy 's strategically valuable targets . this paralyses the other side 's command systems at the start of the war and turns the enemy 's conventional forces , even if they are superior , into a " slab of meat on a cutting board . " 
in the $number persian gulf war , the $number kosovo war and the $number iraq war , the us military did not concern itself with how many planes the opponent had , but rather the range of its own tomahawk cruise missiles . 
even if iran 's government has prepared for a possible air attack and has begun to take steps to reinforce its air - defense capabilities , iran , which fought to a stalemate in an eight - year war with iraq , seems not to have fully understood the true meaning of modern hi - tech warfare . 
with the progress of the us military 's military transformation in recent years , the us military 's air - attack operations are completely different from the carpet bombing of the vietnam war and instead rely on full - depth air assaults with various hi - tech weapons and modern information technology . 
faced with this kind of air assault , how long iran 's land - based air defense systems can hold out is an unknown . 
source : cri online - " world news journal " 
