& lt ; headline & gt ; joining hands with google to battle microsoft : will dell charge microsoft " top - shelf fees " ? 
& lt ; poster & gt ; yun feiquan 
dell inc . ( us : dell ) and google confirmed on tuesday that dell is currently testing pcs installed with google 's software pack . 
this step could form a significant threat to microsoft 's ( microsoftcorp . , msft ) dominant position in the pc software market . 
dell spokesman jess blackburn said the company is currently evaluating google 's software . 
after the software has been installed , the pc - user will be able to use the software to conduct searches on the internet as well as search through information stored on the pc . 
blackburn confirmed that the software being evaluated by the company includes a google - supported dell homepage , a google desktop search tool and a google tool bar . 
at the same time , google spokesman jon murchinson also confirmed that the company was working with dell in testing a software bundle developed by google . 
earlier , a report in the wall street journal had said that it upstart google was in talks with dell and hewlett - packard in an attempt to convince the computer manufacturing giants to install google software in their computers . 
according to an insider quoted by the wall street journal , in order to achieve this end , google may have to pay up to us $ 3 bn over the next three years . 
however , the two companies have not disclosed any relevant details . 
furthermore , hp still refuses to issue a comment . 
microsoft spokesman neil charney refused to comment on the above information . 
currently , microsoft is planning to launch a search tool for the next generation of its windows operating system and strengthen the development of its online business . 
on the day of the news statement , shares in google fell another $number to us $ $number . 
shares in microsoft fell that day by $number to close at us $ $number . 
some analysts say that google is eagerly seeking to expand in a direction beyond web searching and that linking up with dell and other pc giants could prompt google to threaten microsoft in its core businesses . 
matt rosoff , analyst with the market research firm directions on microsoft , says that microsoft is unquestionably concerned and worried by google 's eagerness to expand into other sources of revenue . 
but other analysts strongly disagree . 
charles di bona , analyst with market research firm sanford c. bernstein , says that it is still too early to talk about google shaking windows ' dominate position . 
reporter handbook : is google shaking up microsoft 's landscape ? 
hui zhengyi 
without doubt , the computer has become a necessity in modern man 's life and work . 
but while everybody has become familiar with operating computers , only a small portion of people understand the working principles behind a computer . 
just like with an " idiot " camera , if the interface is friendly and the software is convenient and quick to use , the vast majority of " newbies " can find their way around the black box that is a computer . 
for this reason , the software originally installed by the pc manufacturer more often than not determines the usage habits of most consumers . 
indeed , it was through this measure that microsoft took firm hold of the market for pc operating systems . 
now , microsoft 's new rival , google , also intends to use this method to take a piece of the pie . 
in regards to this , a well - known organization in the taiwanese economic media recently made an interesting analogy . 
" dell , hp and other computer manufacturers are starting to treat the computers they produce as supermarket shelves and they are charging 'top shelf fees ' to software companies . 
the winning bidder can cause its software to appear in the 'crucial ten minutes ' after the user turns on the new computer and thereby induce the consumer to use their product . 
this type of fee method is like the top - shelve fees charged by supermarkets to food companies . " 
without doubt , this phenomenon indicates that microsoft 's control is being shaken . 
microsoft 's managers have warned bill gates , saying that if google starts paying money to pc manufacturers in order to have computers shipped with google software installed , then microsoft 's position as overlord will ultimately be threatened . 
whatever the final outcome , microsoft 's easy days safely perched at the top of the ladder might become history . 
after all , keeping a market is much more difficult than creating a market . 
