& lt ; headline & gt ; dalai lama 's envoys hold closed door talks with chinese officials 
& lt ; poster & gt ; beili of the cgp 
dalai lama 's envoys hold closed door talks with chinese officials . 
dalai lama stressed he wants autonomy , not independence , for tibet . 
envoys of tibet 's exiled spiritual leader the dalai lama are in china for closed door talks with chinese officials . details have not yet been released . 
this is $number official meeting since china and the dalai lama 's exiled government resumed contacts $date . 
but , as in the past , the two sides are meeting behind closed doors . no details have yet been disclosed . 
reporters say the two sides have held talks on several occasions , but so far there have been no tangible results . 
the dalai lama , who is in exile in northern india , says he wants autonomy , not independence , for tibet . 
china has refused to comment on the talks between the two sides . 
but analysts say beijing wants dialogue , partly because it fears the death of the $number - year - old spiritual leader in exile could lead to heightened sentiments among tibetans unhappy with china rule . 
cultural identity 
the delegation from the dalai lama 's exiled government is led by lodi gyaltsen gyari . he was also the lead delegate in earlier talks . 
a spokesman for the tibetan government - in - exile said the round of talks that they had with chinese officials in switzerland $date were very " intensive and frank " and this has given the tibetan people hope . 
the spokesman said their ultimate hope is to resolve the relevant issues on the basis of a negotiated settlement with the chinese leadership so that the tibetan people will have the freedom to preserve what is important to them , which is their cultural identity . 
